      <!-- Why Choose SuperLocalMemory -->
      <div style="background: var(--color-bg-secondary); border: 2px solid var(--color-accent); border-radius: var(--border-radius); padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Why Choose SuperLocalMemory V2?</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-2" style="gap: 1.5rem;">
          <div>
            <h3 style="color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1rem;">✅ You Should Choose It If:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>You value <strong>privacy and data ownership</strong></li>
              <li>You want <strong>zero ongoing costs</strong></li>
              <li>You need <strong>universal IDE support</strong> (Cursor, Windsurf, Claude, VS Code, etc.)</li>
              <li>You prefer <strong>local-first architecture</strong></li>
              <li>You want <strong>pattern learning</strong> and identity profiles</li>
              <li>You need <strong>GDPR/HIPAA compliance</strong></li>
              <li>You work in <strong>air-gapped environments</strong></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">❌ Consider Alternatives If:</h3>
